# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

## [Unreleased]

### Added
- Added a desktop Tkinter app for importing Project 1999 inventory `.txt` files into Excel.
- Added support for importing multiple files into one workbook.
- Added one worksheet per imported file.
- Added an Item Summary sheet that combines matching items across all imported files.
- Added Project 1999 wiki links for item names.
- Added default keyword highlighting for Crown, Throne, Squire, and Knight.
- Added support for custom highlight keywords in the app UI.
- Added batch files for running the app directly and building console/windowed executables.

### Changed
- Changed re-import behavior so existing sheets are replaced instead of duplicated.
- Changed row highlighting to apply across the full row instead of only one cell.
- Changed summary ordering so highlighted items appear at the top.
- Changed the summary sheet to also use keyword-based highlighting.
- Changed workbook writing logic to rebuild the summary sheet on each import.

### Fixed
- Fixed row highlight offset issues where formatting appeared on the wrong row.
- Fixed missing highlighting on the Item Summary sheet.
- Fixed duplicate Excel table-name collisions by generating unique workbook-wide table names.
- Fixed repeated import issues when files with existing sheet names were added again.
- Fixed packaging workflow by providing separate debug and windowed build scripts for PyInstaller.
